{
  "texts": [
    "However, they are all part of the broader scientific system, which imposes overarching standards such as peer review, publication ethics, and the pursuit of truth.",
    "This primary system maintains the relationship between these fields by providing a unified framework for communication and evaluation.",
    "However, this ecology is constantly subject to change and adaptation as new differentiations emerge within the primary system and its subsystems, as complexity increases to reflect the absolute indeterminacy of the systems' environment.",
    "These structural dynamics are what Luhmann refers to as structural coupling (Luhmann 2012).",
    "The term 'ecology' in this context refers to the dynamic and interdependent nature of systems within their environment."
  ]
}